raw_data.title: Associate Systems Engineer
raw_data.description: Entry level engineer responsible for providing implementation services and tech support to support more senior engineers in project implementation and configuration tasks. Also responsible for support of in-house systems.

raw_data.title: Systems Engineer
raw_data.description: Mid-level engineer responsible for leading and participating in small to mid-level projects, as well as assisting in larger projects under the direction of a more senior engineer assigned as a project lead. Other responsibilities include configuration and maintenance of in-house demo lab hardware and maintaining required technical certifications to support sales and services.

raw_data.title: Senior Systems Engineer
raw_data.description: Senior engineer responsible for leading complex mid to enterprise level projects, mentoring junior level engineers, monitoring technical project progress, assisting Solutions Architects when required, and documentation production and accuracy for client systems. Other responsibilities include configuration and maintenance of in-house demo lab hardware and maintaining required technical certifications to support sales and services.

raw_data.title: Associate Solutions Architect
raw_data.description: Entry level Solutions Architect responsible for scoping effort, and drafting design for specific technical area of responsibility (network, server, storage, etc.), for inclusion into overall client solution to satisfy client business goals.

raw_data.title: Solutions Architect
raw_data.description: Mid-level Solutions Architect responsible for applying advanced analysis skills and experience in principals of solutions design to define appropriate client solution, scope the effort, and provide technical leadership in sales pursuits. Also, may be responsible for multiple technical areas of responsibility, and/or for the overall design of the solution and mapping client business requirements to systems/technical requirements.

raw_data.title: Senior Solutions Architect
raw_data.description: Senior level Solutions Architect responsible for applying advanced analysis skills and experience in principals of solutions design to define appropriate client solution, scope the effort, and provide technical leadership in sales pursuits. Responsible for the overall design of the solution and mapping client business requirements to systems/technical requirements to provide a complete client solution.

raw_data.title: IT Project Manager
raw_data.description: The Project Manager will work directly with the systems engineering teams across the company providing Project Management for all clients, as well as internal IT sources requesting engineering services through IT infrastructure design and implementation engagements. Utilizing project management methodologies, knowledge, and expertise, they will provide Project Management oversight for small to enterprise-scale technology implementations. The Project Management oversight will enforce project timeline and budget adherence, resulting in increased client satisfaction, improved delivery and implementation practices, and project profitability.
